<header>
	Tips for Part 2 of the IELTS Speaking test - your 1-2 minute talk.
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../Media/MM_SP_002.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff"><b>Tip 1</b></font>Read what is required. Try and think of at last two things to say for each question.</p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff"><b>Tip 2</b></font>Don't say you cannot talk about the topic. </p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff"><b>Tip 3</b></font>Don't go off the topic.</p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff"><b>Tip 4</b></font>Don't wait to be prompted by the examiner.</p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff"><b>Tip 5</b></font>Show that you are willing to discuss anything, even if you know very little about it. Use your strategies to 'talk round' it.</p><p align="left"><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0000ff"><b>Tip 6</b></font>Give your own opinion about the question and ideas.</p><p align="left"><font size="2"></font></p>
